			<div class="content" id="post-content-1767593">
									

<p>SCP-933-02 has no facial features and doesn't need to breathe; since victims who have lost all their facial features are supposed to pretty much <em>be</em> SCP-933-02 except for not being superhuman, I assumed that they don't need to breathe, either.</p>
<p>What <em>I'd</em> like to know is, <em>why</em> does SCP-933-02 do what it does to people? Is it just to make everyone faceless for no particular reason other than that it <em>can</em>, or is it actually trying to achieve some sort of purpose? Maybe it's actually a slave to SCP-933-01, and SCP-933-01 is a sentient object that <em>feeds</em> on facial features somehow? I mean, Things What Eat You are overdone, but it would work here.</p>
<p>Also, Slender Man. :P</p>
<p>Upvoted because weird humanoid thing + seemingly regular thing that mutilates you. I mean, imagine losing your eyes, ears, nose, and mouth…That's four of the five senses gone right there… *shudder*</p>

